inputs.description: A collection of arguments for invoking getSdk.

parameters.description: Key-value map of query string parameters `sdk_type` properties of the SDK. For SDK Type of `objectivec` or `swift`, a parameter named `classPrefix` is required. For SDK Type of `android`, parameters named `groupId`, `artifactId`, `artifactVersion`, and `invokerPackage` are required. For SDK Type of `java`, parameters named `serviceName` and `javaPackageName` are required.

restApiId.description: Identifier of the associated REST API.

sdkType.description: Language for the generated SDK. Currently `java`, `javascript`, `android`, `objectivec` (for iOS), `swift` (for iOS), and `ruby` are supported.

stageName.description: Name of the Stage that will be exported.

outputs.description: A collection of values returned by getSdk.

contentDisposition.description: Content-disposition header value in the HTTP response.

contentType.description: Content-type header value in the HTTP response.

id.description: The provider-assigned unique ID for this managed resource.
